h1.p: All technological transformations require tools. Tool provision is neither structurally nor logically related to consumption. Firstly,its connection point differs from consumed inputs; and secondly,the tool belongs to a different supply chain. Capital markets service innovation by moving money across supply chains for profit; the Production Network offers an alternative targeted route motivated by productivity gain.
